column5: I couldn't help but notice there were numerous members listing Neil Young as one of their favourites. Here is a rare link of Neil Young busking on the streets of Glasgow. The song "Old Laughing Lady".  Didn't think much of it the 1st time I watched it, but took a 2nd look and realized how incredible it must have been to witness it live.  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=900Jei5vIsU
Hey, thanks for sharing that.  That was great!  I've always loved Neil Young.  Joey
Awesome,   I love listening to Neil, Lightfoot, and the Doobies on a dark nite with a brew and a camp fire.
That was great. I'm a big Neil fan.  Oddly, I never liked the over-produced studio version of that song.
that was really sweet. Thanks for posting that.  Neil is my favorite musician, and i had never seen that video before....made my day!
thats unbelievable, ppl didnt have a clue who he was.. Thats classic Neil thats 4 sure
When a kid, never thought I'd say anything good about Neil.  Times sure change.  Thanks for the link dood.
Real cool video,  Niel rules!!!!  "Neil" that is.....
